<p>Why do I get an error when firing <code>printGenericType(new Box[Master]())</code> , and do not get any error in case if I run <code>printGenericType(new Box())</code> on <code>new Box[Master]()</code>?</p>  <pre><code>object VarianceExample extends App {    new Box[Master]().printGenericType(new Box()) // ok   new Box().printGenericType(new Box[Master]()) // fail  }  class Box[T &gt;: Tool](implicit m: Manifest[T]) {   def printGenericType(box: Box[T]) = {     println(s"Generic type is [$m] - $box")   } }  class Master class Tool   extends Master class Hammer extends Tool </code></pre>